:::summary
God the Father — Heavenly Father, the Almighty, the Creator of heaven and earth — is the first person of the Godhead and the supreme being of the Christian faith. He is the loving Father who sent his Son Jesus Christ to redeem mankind, the God who covenanted with Abraham, who spoke through Moses, who is worshipped by billions across the world's great monotheistic faiths. To know God the Father is the beginning and the end of Christian theology, the goal of human existence, and the source of all that is good, true, and beautiful.
:::

